.TH G510-CTL 1 "2026-03-28" "g510 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
g510-ctl \- command-line interface to the G510 daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B g510-ctl
\fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B g510-ctl
communicates with the running
.BR g510-daemon (1)
via D-Bus to control the keyboard.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show daemon status: keyboard model, active bank, game mode, profile, RGB, LCD screen.
.TP
.B color \fIr g b\fR | \fIname\fR
Set RGB backlight color. Named colors: red, green, blue, orange, purple, cyan, yellow, white, off.
.TP
.B lcd \fIscreen\fR
Set LCD screen. Screens: clock, sysinfo, nowplaying, custom.
.TP
.B profile list|switch|create|delete [\fIname\fR]
Manage profiles.
.TP
.B macro list [\fIbank\fR|ALL]
List all bound macros in a bank.
.TP
.B macro get \fIkey bank\fR
Show the macro bound to a key/bank.
.TP
.B macro set \fIkey bank type value\fR
Bind a macro. Types: shell, keystroke, text, script.
.TP
.B macro delete \fIkey bank\fR
Unbind a macro.
.TP
.B macro clear \fIbank\fR|ALL
Remove all macros from a bank or all banks.
.TP
.B completions bash|zsh
Print shell completion script.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.B g510-ctl color orange
.PP
.B g510-ctl macro set G1 M1 shell "xterm -e htop"
.PP
.B g510-ctl macro set G2 M1 keystroke "ctrl+shift+t"
.PP
.B g510-ctl profile switch gaming
.PP
.B source <(g510-ctl completions bash)
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR g510-daemon (1),
.BR g510-gui (1)
